'''Resonant Neurobiology''' is the working hypothesis that the abstract category of '''[[Resonant]]''' — individuals with elevated ψ-field coupling — has '''measurable neurophysiological signatures''' that can be detected with standard wearable instrumentation.

This page defines those proposed signatures so that [[Resonant Finder]] models, [[Resonant Pipeline]] screening, and [[Psi Recorder]] telemetry have a concrete, testable phenotype to validate against.

